Someone made the good point that it's not really women's "fault" that they do not have children and marry very late, because most young women do dream of being mothers and family life, but no one is really proposing to them or giving them children so there's not much they can do.

So who's really at fault? The answer is there is simply an evil spirit over the age. I don't intend this as a metaphor whatsoever. There's a literal entity floating in the air that's doing it. Spreading corruption and pestilence over the land. Someone needs to go and fuck it up.

But Varg Vikernes' advice of "live in a tent in the woods for free, bathe in a river, work as a construction worker and collect money until you can afford to buy enough land to live off from, and only then get married" rings just a bit too true. It's natural to desire security.
